---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import PageHero from "../../components/PageHero.astro";
import CtaBand from "../../components/CtaBand.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Patrol & Guard Tours — Checkpoint Verification & Route Tracking | SYAG"
  description="Verify guard presence at every checkpoint with NFC, QR, and GPS. Track patrol routes, detect missed checkpoints, and generate automated patrol compliance reports."
>
  <PageHero
    label="Patrol & Tours"
    headline="Every checkpoint. Every patrol. <span style='color:#4ade80'>Verified</span>."
    subheadline="SYAG Patrol ensures guards complete their assigned routes — and proves it. NFC tags, QR codes, and GPS tracking give you irrefutable patrol records for every shift."
  />

  <section class="space-y-6">
    <h2 class="quartr-heading text-3xl font-semibold text-white">Three ways to verify <span style="color:#35E0FF">presence</span></h2>
    <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
      <div class="glass-card space-y-3">
        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-white">NFC Tags</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-white/60">
          Place NFC tags at checkpoints around your facility. Guards tap their phone to scan.
          Tamper-proof, instant, and works without internet at the moment of scan (syncs when connected).
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="glass-card space-y-3">
        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-white">QR Codes</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-white/60">
          Attach QR code stickers at checkpoints. Guards scan with the SYAG app camera. Lower cost
          than NFC, easy to install anywhere.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="glass-card space-y-3">
        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-white">GPS Geofencing</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-white/60">
          For outdoor patrol routes or vehicle patrols, SYAG auto-verifies checkpoint presence when
          a guard enters a defined GPS zone. No physical tag required.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="text-sm text-white/60">All three methods work on standard Android devices. No dedicated scanning hardware needed.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-6">
    <h2 class="quartr-heading text-3xl font-semibold text-white">Define routes. Track <span style="color:#4ade80">compliance</span>.</h2>
    <div class="glass-card space-y-4">
      <p class="text-sm text-white/60">
        Build patrol routes in the web dashboard by sequencing checkpoints in order. Assign routes
        to specific guards or shifts.
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-white/60">
        <li>Fixed routes: checkpoints must be visited in sequence</li>
        <li>Flexible routes: checkpoints must all be visited, order flexible</li>
        <li>Time-bound routes: each checkpoint has a window — arrive too early or too late, flag it</li>
        <li>Multiple routes per site — perimeter patrol, vehicle patrol, building rounds</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-6">
    <h2 class="quartr-heading text-3xl font-semibold text-white">Catch issues <span style="color:#ef4444">before</span> clients do</h2>
    <div class="glass-card space-y-4">
      <p class="text-sm text-white/60">
        SYAG monitors patrol progress in real time. When a guard misses a checkpoint or falls behind
        on a route, supervisors are notified immediately — before it becomes a compliance issue.
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-white/60">
        <li>Configurable alert threshold per checkpoint (e.g. alert after 15 minutes overdue)</li>
        <li>Notification channels: push, SMS, in-app</li>
        <li>Missed checkpoint auto-creates a watchlist flag for the supervisor to acknowledge</li>
        <li>Pattern detection: flag guards who consistently miss the same checkpoint</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-6">
    <h2 class="quartr-heading text-3xl font-semibold text-white"><span style="color:#4ade80">Automated</span> patrol compliance reports</h2>
    <div class="glass-card space-y-4">
      <p class="text-sm text-white/60">At the end of every shift, SYAG generates a full patrol report automatically:</p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-white/60">
        <li>All checkpoints visited, time-stamped</li>
        <li>Missed checkpoints with reason (if logged by guard)</li>
        <li>GPS track overlay on facility map</li>
        <li>Comparison to scheduled route</li>
        <li>Guard compliance rate for the shift</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-sm text-white/60">
        Reports are available in the dashboard, exportable as PDF, and can be scheduled for automatic
        delivery by email.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="glass-card space-y-3">
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-white/40">Connects with</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      {[
        { label: "Guard Management", href: "/products/guard-management" },
        { label: "Incident Management", href: "/products/incidents" },
        { label: "Flow Automation", href: "/products/flow" },
      ].map((link) => (
        <a href={link.href} class="rounded-full border border-white/20 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-white/60 hover:border-white/50 hover:text-white/80">
          {link.label}
        </a>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <CtaBand
    headline="See patrol verification <span style='color:#ff8a3c'>in action</span>."
    primaryLabel="Request a demo →"
    primaryHref="/demo"
  />
</Layout>
